{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Butt's Way | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Aston Rowant]], [[Oxfordshire]] | establishment = 1987 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1987-1999 & 2006-2007 | club1 = [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]] | date = 15 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/286.html Ground profile }}
'''Butt's Way''' is a [[cricket]] ground between the villages of [[Aston Rowant]] and [[Kingston Blount]], [[Oxfordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1987, when [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]] played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match on the ground against [[Buckinghamshire County Cricket Club|Buckinghamshire]]. From 1987 to 1998, the ground hosted 5 Minor Counties Championship matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/286_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Butt's Way]</ref> The ground has also held 4 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches, the last of which came in 2007 against Buckinghamshire.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/286_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on Butt's Way]</ref>
The ground has held 2 [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches, the first of which saw Oxfordshire play [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]] in the [[1994 NatWest Trophy]]. The second List-A match came in 1996 with Oxfordshire playing [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] in the [[1996 NatWest Trophy]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/286_a.html List A Matches played on Butt's Way]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home of [[Aston Rowant Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Home Counties Premier Cricket League]].<ref>[http://astonrowantcricket.com/ Aston Rowant Cricket Club]</ref>
