{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Guillermo Vargas Roldán | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = [[San Ramón, Costa Rica|San Ramón]], [[Alajuela]], [[Costa Rica]] | fullname = Estadio Guillermo Vargas Roldán | former_names = | location = | coordinates = {{Coord|10|5|30.16|N|84|28|34.58|W|scale:3125_region:CR|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1961 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = City of [[San Ramón, Costa Rica|San Ramón]] | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 4,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 100 x 72 [[metre|m]] | acreage = | tenants = [[Asociación Deportiva Ramonense]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Estadio Guillermo Vargas Roldán''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Alajuela]], [[Costa Rica]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Asociación Deportiva Ramonense]]. The stadium holds up to 4,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/middle_america/countries/costa_rica.shtml |title=Stadiums in Costa Rica|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=9 November 2011}}</ref>
The stadium was named in December 1978 after former Ramonense club president Guillermo Vargas Roldán, who died in April 2014, aged 82.<ref>[http://www.nacion.com/deportes/futbol-costa-rica/futbol-nacional-perdio-papa-Ramonense_0_1410059025.html Guillermo Vargas Roldán El fútbol nacional perdió al papá de Ramonense] - Nación {{es|icon}}</ref> He had been president of the club for a record 22 years.
