{{refimprove|date=February 2014}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Gan Ner Sports Hall | nickname = | location = [[Gan Ner]] | image = Gan Ner Sports Hall.png | opened = 2008 | renovated = | expanded = 2010 | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Gilboa Regional Council]] | operator = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Hapoel Gilboa Galil]] | capacity = 2,057 }} The '''Gan Ner Sports Hall''' ({{lang-he|היכל הספורט גן נר}}) is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Gan Ner]], [[Israel]], And is the home of basketball team [[Hapoel Gilboa Galil]].
When the arena inaugurated in 2008 it held 900 places. The arena has been expended to 2,057 in 2010 to meet [[ULEB]] criteria for hosting a game in the [[Eurocup Basketball|Eurocup]] competition. The arena has not been approved even after the expansion, as ULEB demend a capacity of 3,000 seats.<ref>[http://m.sport5.co.il/Pages/Article.aspx?articleId=102905 Galil Gilboa will sue ULEB]</ref>
In April 2012, The arena has hosted the [[2011–12 BIBL season|2011–12 BIBL]] final four, which saw the home team take the cup.<ref>[http://balkanleague.net/en/schedule.php?season_id=15&champ_id=43 2011–12 BIBL Final Four]</ref>
