{{Infobox venue | name = Montego Bay Sports Complex | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former names = | address = | location = [[Montego Bay|Catherine Hall, Montego Bay]] | coordinates = {{coord|18.457930|-77.921388|type:landmark|name=Montego Bay Sports Complex|display=it}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|2010|06|5|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.udcja.com/captions/udc-officially-opens-montego-bay-sports-complex|title=UDC Officially Opens Montego Bay Sports Complex|publisher=udcja.com|date=5 June 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106194357/http://www.udcja.com/captions/udc-officially-opens-montego-bay-sports-complex|archivedate=6 January 2015|df=}}</ref> | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 7,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded =
}} '''Montego Bay Sports Complex''' (sometimes referred to as '''Catherine Hall Sports Complex''') is a multi-purpose sports stadium in the Catherine Hall area of the city of [[Montego Bay]], [[Jamaica]]. It is also the former home field for [[Montego Bay United F.C.|Montego Bay United]]. The stadium capacity is approximately 7,000.
In July 2014, it was announced as a host venue for the CONCACAF U-20 Championship.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jamaica Set to Host CONCACAF Under-20 Championships in January|url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/jamaica-set-to-host-concacaf-under-20-championships-in-january|publisher=CONCACAF.com|accessdate=23 July 2014|date=23 July 2014}}</ref>
In October 2014, the venue was announced the host for the final round of the [[2014 Caribbean Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Men's Caribbean Cup fixtures updated|url=http://www.cfufootball.org/index.php/caribbean-cup/9522-men-s-caribbean-cup-fixtures-updated|publisher=CFUFootball.org|accessdate=3 October 2014|date=2 October 2014}}</ref>
Jamaica hosted the Under-20 Championship in January 2015, with the Montego Bay Stadium one of the two stadium used for the tournament. The ground hosted a total of 24 games, including the final between Panama and Mexico on January 24.
